    <!-- Formula help texts -->
    <string name="home_help_fick"><![CDATA[FORMULAS
• CaO₂ = 1.34 × Hb × SaO₂ + 0.0031 × PaO₂
• CvO₂ = 1.34 × Hb × SvO₂ + 0.0031 × PvO₂
• ΔC(a−v)O₂ = CaO₂ − CvO₂
• CO (L/min) = VO₂ / (ΔC(a−v)O₂ × 10)
• CI (L/min/m²) = CO / BSA
• SV (mL) = (CO × 1000) / HR

UNITS / NOTES
• Hb in g/dL. Saturations in % (convert if needed).
• SvO₂ ideally: mixed venous sample from pulmonary artery.
• 0.0031×PO₂ is usually small and can be omitted if blood gases are not available.
• VO₂: ideally measured; if estimated, depends on formula/sex/body size.]]></string>

    <string name="home_help_svr"><![CDATA[FORMULAS
• SVR (Wood Units) = (MAP − CVP) / CO
• SVR (dyn·s·cm⁻⁵) = SVR(WU) × 80

UNITS / NOTES
• MAP and CVP (or RAP) in mmHg; CO in L/min.
• If non-invasive MAP: MAP ≈ (SBP + 2×DBP)/3.
• Use a consistent CO method for comparability.]]></string>

    <string name="home_help_cpo"><![CDATA[FORMULAS
• CPO (W) = (MAP × CO) / 451
• CPI (W/m²) = CPO / BSA

UNITS / NOTES
• MAP in mmHg; CO in L/min.
• 451 is the conversion factor to Watts.
• Always interpret in clinical context.]]></string>

    <string name="home_help_papi"><![CDATA[FORMULAS
• PAPi = (PASP − PADP) / RAP

UNITS / NOTES
• PASP, PADP, RAP in mmHg.
• RAP = right atrial pressure (RAP/CVP).]]></string>

